						               													<description>Ponies is a horse racing game with dice.  Seven dice are included with the game, 6 with letters and 1 normal die.  Players start with an equal amount of money (in 1, 5, 10, 20 and 50 unit demoninations) and all start with a 5 unit in the stake fund.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each players take turns at one roll of all seven dice.  The following word combinations are possible:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;WIN - Player takes all units in stake.  This then starts a new game.&amp;#10;PLACE - Player collects 1/2 of the units in the stake.&amp;#10;SHOW - Player collects 1/3 of the units in the stake.&amp;#10;LEAD - Player collects 10 times the number of units indicated by nunber on normal die from the stake.&amp;#10;PACE or RACE - Player collects 5 times the number of units indicated by number on the normal die from the stake.&amp;#10;REAR - Player neither collects or donates.&amp;#10;If none of the above words appear on role, player then donates number of units indicated on the normal die to the stake.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Player can never collect more money than is in the stake.  When there is no more money in the stake, all players donate five unites apiece to the stake.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game continues until someone gets WIN.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Alternate game play: Only play with rules for WIN, PLACE or SHOW.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
